2154.subject: NURS
2154.descrlong:
Introduces the theoretical basis for nursing in community health, public health, and global health. Promoting health, managing and/or delivering care in a variety of community settings is emphasized. Cultural humility, health maintenance, and issues of under-served populations are also addressed.

[Prereq: (NURS 300 and NURS 306 and NURS 321 and NURS 330 and NURS 340 and NURS 360 and NURS 410 and NURS 421) and (Coreq: NURS 499S) and (Restricted to NURS Majors Only)]
